Preheat broiler to high (or #oven{} to 500 degrees). Wash and dry all produce. Halve, peel, and dice @yellow onion{1}(halved, peeled, diced). Peel @carrots{1}(peeled and quartered lengthwise, then crosswise into ¼-inch pieces). Dice @Yukon Gold potatoes{12%oz}(diced into ½-inch cubes). Pat @chicken breast strips{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with @salt{}, @pepper{}, and half the @Fry Seasoning{1%tbsp}.

Place potatoes in a #medium bowl{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until potatoes are tender, about ~{15%minutes}. Drain and return to #pot{}. Mash with a #potato masher{} or #fork{} until smooth. Stir in @butter{2%tbsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. 

> TIP: If potatoes are too thick, stir in a splash of water.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook, stirring, until browned and cooked through, ~{5-6%minutes}. Transfer to a #cutting board{}. If necessary, cut into bite-sized pieces. Place carrot in a medium bowl with a splash of water. Cover with #plastic wrap{}. Microwave on high until soft, ~{3-4%minutes}. Drain.

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for chicken over medium-high heat. Add onion and cook, stirring, until lightly browned and softened, ~{4-5%minutes}. Stir in @butter{1%tbsp} until melted, then stir in @flour{1%tbsp} and remaining Fry Seasoning. Cook for ~{1%minute}. Gradually whisk in 1 cup water and @chicken stock concentrate{1}. Reduce heat to medium and simmer until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Stir in @peas{4%oz}, chicken, and carrot. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Transfer filling to an #8-by-8-inch baking dish{} (use a #9-by-13-inch baking dish{} for 4 servings). Evenly top with mashed potatoes. Evenly sprinkle with @cheddar cheese{½%cup}. Broil until cheese has melted, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> TIP: It's okay if the potatoes don't reach the edge of the baking dish.